rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all batteries. Batteries are the devices that convert stored chemical energy into electrical energy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to the mso:engineering.battery_cell_type, which are the types of electrochemical cells used in the battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to its mso:engineering.battery_size.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to its maximum charge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to the maximum energy stored in the battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Energy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to its mass.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to the mso:engineering.material_composition entities collecting the type and amount of materials used in this battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chemistry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to the number of cells it contains. The cells are the devices that generate, or facilitate the generation of, electrical energy in the battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Cells

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery to its electrical potential difference in Volts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voltage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all battery cell types. These are the types of electrochemical cells developed for use in batteries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Cell Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.battery_cell_type to the mso:engineering.battery(ies) that are use this battery cell type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batteries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.battery_cell_type to its mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Sizes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_cell_type to the boolean value indicating whether or not the battery is rechargeable.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rechargeable
Battery Shape Format
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use the broader mso:common.shape. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[mso:common.shape]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: battery_sizes
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to common.shape. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all battery sizes. Size is part of the battery nomenclature and is one of the physical characteristics standardized.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size to the mso:engineering.battery(ies) of this size.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batteries

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size to its mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation type that collects the data on the differing electrical properties dependent on the cell type used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Variations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:battery_size to the diameter, for cylinder or button-shaped batteries, or width, for a cuboid-shaped battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diameter or Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size to its height.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size to its length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size to its mso:engineering.battery_shape_format.
Note that mso:engineering.battery_shape_format is deprecated, and the expected type for this property will change to mso:common.shape in the future.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shape format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on the variations for a given battery size. Data includes the capacity, the battery cell type, and the voltage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Size Cell Variation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation type to the name used for the variation in the ANSI and/or NEDA standards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: ANSI/NEDA Name

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to the mso:engineering.battery_cell_type used for this variation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to its capacity, which is the charge deliverable for batteries of this variation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to the maximum energy stored in batteries of this variation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Energy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to its name in the IEC 60086 standard
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IEC 60086 Name

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to its mso:engineering.battery_size.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.battery_size_cell_variation to its voltage, which is the maximum electric potential difference achievable under normal operating conditions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voltage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides subscribers access to cable and/or satellite television.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cable and Satellite Television Provider

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all engine carburetor. Carburetors are the devices in engines that blend air and fuel for internal combustion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Carburetor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.carburetor to the description of any shims added to the needle in the carburetor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all channel access methods. These are the means by which several terminals connected to the same multi-point transmission medium transmit over it and share its capacity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Channel Access Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The channel access method that this method is based on, or is a variation of.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all clutches. Clutches are the mechanical devices that transmit power from one component to another. Clutches are used when this transmission must be controlled in its amount or over time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clutch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all drive types. Drive types are the means of transferring mechanical power from the place of generation to its application place of work. Important sub-classes include belt drives and chain drives.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drive Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all electrical current types. These are the categories of electrical currents like direct current and alternating current.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electric Current Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides electricity to the buildings of its customers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electricity Provider

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration type representing the set of energy types. This includes natural gas, oil, and electricity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Energy Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the electricity production for energy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electricity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the natural gas production for energy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Natural Gas

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the oil production for energy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Oil

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all engines. An engine is any machine that converts energy into mechanical motion. Types of engines include internal and external combustion engines and electric motors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its mso:engineering.engine_category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an internal combustion engine to the ratio of the maximum to minimum volume in a cylinder of the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compression Ratio

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an engine to a textual description of the kind of cooling mechanism that is used by the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cooling Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an engine to its number of cylinders (tubes in which pistons of the engine move).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinders

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its mso:engineering.engine_designer(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its mso:engineering.engine_energy_source, the fuel or batteries used by this engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Energy Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to the date the engine had its first run.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Ran

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its dry mass, its weight, in kg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its maximum power in kiloWatts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an internal combustion engine to a textual description of the device used to rotate the engine so that the engine can operate under its own power.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Starter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an engine to a textual description of the arrangement of values in the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valve Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an engine to its number of valves (openings in engine cylinders that allow a fuel-air mixture to be drawn into the cylinders).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valves

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an engine to the number of valves of the engine (mso:engineering.engine.valves) divided by the number of cylinders of the engine (mso:engineering.engine.cylinders).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valves per Cylinder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to its variations.
Property relating an mso:engineering.engine to other mso:engineering.engine, of which the first is a variant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Variation of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all engine types. These are the groupings of engines based on shared characteristics. Included in this type are 'diesel engine' and 'induction motor'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.engine_category to the mso:engineering.engine which fall into this category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: More specific categories which fall into this category
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sub-categories

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all methods of cooling engines, typically using air or liquids.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Cooling Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.engine_cooling_method to the mso:engineering.piston_engine(s) using this method for cooling.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all engine designers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.engine_designer to the mso:engineering.engine(s) the agent designed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines Designed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all engine energy sources. These are the types of fuels an engine converts into mechanical motion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Energy Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.engine_energy_source to the mso:engineering.engine(s) using this energy.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all engine parts. These are the pieces of an engine needed to make it work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Part

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all engine technologies. These are the engine technologies that are associated with combustion engines. Important sub-classes include fuel system technology and engine cooling technology.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Technology

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of types of engines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all fuel delivery methods, the means by which fuel is moved throughout the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel Delivery Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.fuel_delivery_method to the mso:engineering.piston_engine(s) using this means of fuel delivery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all fuel tanks. These are the containers in an engine system that store fuel and distribute it to the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel Tank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a fuel tank to the amount of fuel, in liters, that the fuel tank can hold.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides subscribers access to the Internet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Internet Service
Location with mains power
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Unnecessary type; use location.location or one of its subtypes instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: mains_power_standards
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to location.location. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all locks. Locks are the waterway devices used for raising and lowering boats between stretches of water of different levels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lock

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.lock to the mso:geography.body_of_water on which it is placed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Body of Water

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.lock to its general mso:engineering.lock_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lock Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.lock to the rise, which is the change in water-level effected by the lock.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rise

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all lock systems. These are the sets of mso:engineering.locks used to work together.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lock System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.lock_system to the number of mso:engineering.locks in the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.lock_system to the distance between the lowest end and highest end of the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Rise

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all lock types. These are the general groupings of locks, the waterway devices. Subsets include 'boat lift' and 'pound lock'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lock Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data for a particular mains electricity system, including the AC frequency, the nominal voltage, and the location of the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mains Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.mains_power system to the nominal frequency at which the AC current is supplied.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: AC Frequency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.mains_power system to the mso:engineering.power_plug_standard_type(s) that are compatible with the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compatible Plugs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.mains_power system to the region or country of use. Note mso:engineering.location_with_mains_power is deprecated, and this expected type will change to location.location or one of its subtypes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.mains_power system to the voltage used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nominal System Voltage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all materials. Materials are the tangible substances that make up physical objects.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The hyponym material of this. e.g. Carbon steel and Stainless steel are subclasses of Steel
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Child material class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data for the material composition for a given physical object, including the mass and the material type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Material Composition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The mass of the material used in this component
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The specific material used
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides natural gas to the buildings of its customers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Natural Gas Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all pipelines. Pipelines are the conduits for liquid and gas transport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pipeline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.pipeline to the substance or material it transports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all piston configurations. These are the engine configurations categorized by the layout of the pistons.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Piston Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.piston_configuration to the mso:engineering.piston_engine(s) that have this configuration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_configuration to the number of individual pistons within it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Pistons

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all reciprocating engines. These are the engines that use one or more reciprocating pistons to convert pressure into a rotating motion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Piston Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its brake specific fuel consumption in grams per kiloWatt hours. This is a measure of the engine's fuel efficiency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brake Specific Fuel Consumption

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its volume in liters
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to the angle of the engine's cylinders.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinder Angle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.pistn_engine to the maximum bore diameter of the piston cylinders.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinder Bore

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies in cubic meters the total volume traversed by pistons inside the cylinders of the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Displacement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its mso:engineering.engine_cooling_method.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cooling Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its mso:engineering.fuel_delivery_method, the method by which fuel is controlled in the piston cylinders.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel Delivery Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its mso:engineering.piston_configuration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Piston Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to the maximum stroke length of the piston.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Piston Stroke

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to the maximum torque in Newton meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Torque

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to the number of valves per cylinder in an engine type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valves Per Cylinder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.piston_engine to its mso:engineering.valvetrain_configuration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valvetrain Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all power plug standards. These are the inoperability standards guiding characteristics of power plugs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power Plug Standard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug to the boolean value that indicates whether a plug standard requires a fuse.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard to the boolean value that indicates whether or not the plug is grounded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grounded

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard to its mso:engineering.power_plug_standard_type, which are the groupings of plugs, e.g. type A, type B, etc..
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard to a boolean value that indicates whether the plug standard supports polarisation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Polarised

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard to the maximum current allowed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rated Current

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard to its rated voltage. The rated voltage is the voltage that can be safely utilized by a device using this power plug.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rated Voltage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all power plug standard types. These are the groupings of power plug standards along common characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power Plug Standard Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard_type to the mso:engineering.mains_power systems where the plug type can be safely used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compatible Power Systems

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.power_plug_standard_type to the mso:engineering.power_plug_standard(s) that belong to this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Plug Standards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all reaction engines. These are the engines or motors which provide propulsion (thrust) by expelling reaction mass. Included in this type are both jet engines and rocket engines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reaction Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an msoengineering.reaction_engine to its fuel efficiency, with respect to thrust output, in grams of fuel per second-kilonewton.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specific Fuel Consumption

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.reaction_engine to its efficiency as described by the impulse, which is the change in momentum per unit of propellant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specific Impulse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.reaction_engine to its exhaust thrust in kilonewtons.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thrust

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all reactor types. These are the broad groupings of reactors, usually the design of the reactor. Examples include 'boiling water reactor' and 'pressurized water reactor'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reactor Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A research center where science-related experiments, analysis, and testing is conducted. Note that location.scientific_research_base is for remote facilities that are conducting research in the field, while engineering.scientific_laboratory is for facilities conducting contained, e.g. in vitro, research.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scientific Laboratory

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all signal modulation modes. These are the different processes by which one or more of the carrier signal's properties are altered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Signal Modulation Mode

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The modulation of which this is based on and is a variation of.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent modulation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides subscribers landline access to telephone services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Telephone Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization that provides a public service and maintains the infrastructure for the service, e.g. electricity, natural gas, and waste management.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Utility Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all valve gears. These are the mechanisms on steam engines that operates the inlet and exhaust valves to admit steam into the cylinder and allow exhaust steam to escape, respectively, at the correct points in the cycle.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valve Gear

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all valve types. Valves are those devices that regulate, control, or directs the flow of a fluid in a system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valve Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all valvetrain configurations. These are the engine configurations categorized by the layout of the valvetrain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valvetrain Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:engineering.valvetrain_configuration to the mso:engineering.piston_engine(s) with this configuration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that is responsible for picking up solid waste from businesses and residences and delivering it to a landfill.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Waste Management Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all waste treatment methods. These technologies are the means of getting rid of or re-using waste. This includes composting, recycling, and landfills.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Waste Treatment Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that provides businesses and residences access to water and sewer lines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Water and Sewer Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all water treatment methods. These are the methods and technologies by which waste water is cleaned.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Water Treatment Methods

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all wind turbines. These are the devices that convert kinetic energy from wind into electrical power.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Turbine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the length of its blades.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blade Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the number of blades the turbines have.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blades

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the maximum wind speed the turbines can survive.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the mso:engineering.wind_turbine_power_rating the turbine generates at its peak.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Peak Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to a boolean that indicates if the turbine has pitch control, the control that allows the device to change speeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pitch Control

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the mso:engineering.wind_turbine_power_rating the turbine generates at the optimum wind speed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power Rating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the diameter of its rotor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rotor Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to the minimum wind speed the turbines need to start the blades moving.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Startup Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine to its mso:engineering.wind_turbine_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Turbine Types

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting the data on the power ratings for a given wind turbine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Turbine Power Rating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine_power_rating to the amount of power measured in Watts for this optimum wind speed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:engineering.wind_turbine_power_rating to the optimum wind speed for the power rating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all wind turbine types. These are the groupings of wind turbines including 'horizontal axis wind turbine' and 'medium wind turbine'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wind Turbine Types
